    "plan_content": "Here's the complete implementation plan for `ImageTextToTextPipeline`. Everything is contained in **a single file: `src/pipelines.js`** — 4 surgical edits:\n\n---\n\n### What I found\n\n- `AutoModelForImageTextToText` already exists in `src/models.js` (supports Florence-2, LLaVA, Qwen2-VL, etc.) but is **not yet imported** into `src/pipelines.js`\n- `TextImagePipelineConstructorArgs` (the typedef for tokenizer + processor pipelines) is already defined and reusable\n- `src/transformers.js` uses `export * from './pipelines.js'` — the new class is auto-exported with no extra work\n\n### The 4 edits\n\n| # | Where | What |\n|---|-------|------|\n| 1 | Import block (~line 44) | Add `AutoModelForImageTextToText` to the `./models.js` import |\n| 2 | After `DepthEstimationPipeline` (~line 3094) | Insert the full `ImageTextToTextPipeline` class with JSDoc typedefs |\n| 3 | After `\"image-to-text\"` in `SUPPORTED_TASKS` (~line 3255) | Add the `\"image-text-to-text\"` task entry with `onnx-community/Florence-2-base-ft` as default |\n| 4 | `pipeline()` JSDoc list (~line 3427) | Add `\"image-text-to-text\"` entry in alphabetical order |\n\n### Key design decisions for `_call(image, text, generate_kwargs)`\n\n- **Single image** (not batched) — matches `DocumentQuestionAnsweringPipeline` pattern\n- `this.processor(preparedImage)` → `pixel_values`\n- `this.tokenizer(text, { padding, truncation })` → `{ input_ids, attention_mask }` spread into `generate()`\n- `pixel_values` passed alongside text inputs as `model.generate({ ...text_inputs, pixel_values, ...generate_kwargs })`\n- Returns `[{ generated_text: string }]` directly, consistent with requirements",
